@jameschristopher the extra step for the quant might not be an issue if it is straightforward and well documented. Also you suggest to make the `quantile` a new factor index level instead of it being a separate `pd.Series` as it is now, is that right? But then why `forward_returns` deserve a different treatment and it is passed as a separate argument? I am not against your idea, but probably I cannot see the rationale behind it.

Looking at the different sub-tear-sheets created in this PR I can see some of them require `forward_returns`, some require the `quantized factor` and those two sets overlap but not completely. There is also one exception that requires `prices` instead. So, looking at those different needs I cannot say that `forward_returns` could easily be the common denominator to all the function calls. Instead `price` could be, as all the other information can be derived from it.

I feel I have probably missed something though, otherwise you wouldn't have suggested  `forward_returns` as common argument. What would the benefits be of unify the tearsheet API around `forward_returns` ?

