I think the main problem is that GeoJSON doesn't have anything in its specification to express/store SRIDs. The intention of GeoMet is to provide lossless conversions (as much as possible, anyway) between WKT/WKB/GeoJSON.

It may be possible by injecting some "extra" attributes into the GeoJSON structure. Just throwing out ideas. For example:

`SRID=4326;POINT(-44.3 60.1)`

In GeoJSON, this could be:

```
{
  "type": "Point",
  "coordinates": [-44.3, 60.1],
  "meta": {
    "srid": "4326"
  }
}
```

There's no provision in the new [GeoJSON standard](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7946)--as far as I catn tell--for such extensions, but this might be an option.

