I had a look at this and there's two different things in the code. Creating a new `.used_versions` files is currently only done if a custom config file was *not* set explicitly. If there was already a file then the new version string was *always* added anyway. Then, if we're running a previously unseen version of Ganga (based on `.used_versions`), the config file is potentially updated with the new version number (again, only if the config file was *not* set explicitly).

@mjmottram's change here only affects the first of these two so explicitly setting the config file when starting Ganga will now always create a missing `.used_versions` file. I think this makes sense as `update` was only affecting the creation of a `.used_versions`, not its updating.

Personally, I'm happy with this change but I'll give someone else a chance to comment.

