In Relay Mutations the input fields you have in the `NewCatalogItem.Input` are inside the `input` argument in the mutation.

It seems the issue is in the way the mutation is executed in the client side.
So, for your example to work, you would need to execute the following mutation:

```graphql
mutation Catalog {
  newCatalogItem(input: {id: "", store: ""}, clientMutationId:"123") { # and all the other fields
    catalogItem {
      id
    }
  }
}
```

You can find a more detailed example here: https://facebook.github.io/relay/docs/graphql-mutations.html

The tests for graphene Relay mutations might help too: https://github.com/graphql-python/graphene/blob/master/graphene/relay/tests/test_mutation.py#L130

Let me know if that helps! :)

